Femi Fani-Kayode, a former Minister of Aviation has reacted to the report that the Kaduna State Governor, Nasir El-Rufai, has tested positive for coronavirus. DAILY POST had earlier reported that Kaduna State Governor, Nasir El-Rufai, had personally confirmed testing positive for coronavirus Reacting, Kayode took to his twitter account on Saturday to express how sad he was, stating that he wishes him a quick recovery. He wrote, ”I just confirmed that my old friend and brother Governor @elrufai
of Kaduna state has tested positive to Covid 19. ”I sincerely and honestly wish him well and pray for a quick recovery for him just as I do for all the other Nigerians that have tested positive. ” God be with us all.” Nigeria now has 89 confirmed cases of the virus. 